<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="448" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1157,1364]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">
<taxonomicName authority="Bloch" authorityName="Bloch" box="[151,521,1195,1219]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Rhynchobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="haleppensis">
<emphasis box="[151,446,1195,1219]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">Rhynchobdella haleppensis</emphasis>
Bloch
</taxonomicName>
, in 
<bibRefCitation author="Schneider, J. G." box="[565,796,1195,1220]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refId="ref4909" refString="Schneider, J. G. (1801) M. E. Blochii Systema Ichthyologiae iconibus cx illustratum, post obitum auctoris opus inchoatum absoluit, correxit, interpolavit Jo. Gottlob Schneider. Sanderiano, Berolini [Berlin], 584 pp., 110 pls. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 5475805]" type="book" year="1801">Schneider, 1801: 480</bibRefCitation>
is based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Gronovius, L. T. &amp; Zoophylacii Gronoviani" box="[938,1179,1195,1220]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refId="ref3304" refString="Gronovius, L. T. (1763 - 1764) Zoophylacii Gronoviani fasciculus primus exhibens animalia quadrupeda, amphibia atque pisces, quae in museo suo adservat, rite examinavit, systematice disposuit, descripsit atque iconibus illustravit Laur. Theod. Gronovius. Vol. 1 (1763) &amp; Vol. 2 (1764). Sumptibus auctoris [published by author], Lugduni Batavorum [Leiden], pp. 1 - 140, pls. 1 - 17 &amp; pp. 141 - 236. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 50229513]" type="url" year="1763">Gronovius (1763: 132</bibRefCitation>
[n. 402], pl. 8a fig. 1), which itself includes reference to 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, A." box="[515,675,1231,1255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refId="ref3831" refString="Russell, A. (1756) The natural history of Aleppo, and parts adjacents. Containing a description of the city, and the principal natural productions in its neighbourhood; together with an account of the climate, inhabitants, and diseases particularly of the plague, with the methods used by the Europeans for their preservation. Millar, London, viii + 266 + 10 pp., 16 pls. [Publication year on title page erroneously as 1856, https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 25600529] https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 36635" type="book" year="1756">Russell (1756)</bibRefCitation>
. I designate here the specimen model of plate 12 figure 
<quantity box="[1277,1319,1231,1256]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, A." pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refId="ref3831" refString="Russell, A. (1756) The natural history of Aleppo, and parts adjacents. Containing a description of the city, and the principal natural productions in its neighbourhood; together with an account of the climate, inhabitants, and diseases particularly of the plague, with the methods used by the Europeans for their preservation. Millar, London, viii + 266 + 10 pp., 16 pls. [Publication year on title page erroneously as 1856, https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 25600529] https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 36635" type="book" year="1756">Russell (1756)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<typeStatus box="[258,356,1267,1291]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">lectotype</typeStatus>
and this makes 
<taxonomicName authority="Bloch" authorityName="Bloch" box="[527,683,1267,1291]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Rhynchobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="haleppensis">
<emphasis box="[527,683,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">R. haleppensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior objective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walbaum" authorityYear="1792" box="[1016,1123,1267,1291]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Ophidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simack">
<emphasis box="[1016,1123,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">O. simack</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1157,1364]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis box="[199,483,1303,1327]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1777" box="[199,365,1303,1327]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Ophidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mastacembelus">Mastacembelus</taxonomicName>
aleppensis
</emphasis>
of 
<treatmentCitation author="Gunther, A." box="[516,733,1303,1327]" page="541" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" year="1861">
<bibRefCitation author="Gunther, A." box="[516,733,1303,1327]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refId="ref3409" refString="Gunther, A. (1861) Catalogue of the acanthopterygian fishes in the collection of the British Museum. Vol. 3. British Museum, London, xxv + 586 pp. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 8406920]" type="book" year="1861">Günther (1861: 541)</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
is an unjustified emendation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bloch" authorityName="Bloch" box="[1069,1432,1303,1327]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Rhynchobdella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="haleppensis">
<emphasis box="[1069,1361,1303,1327]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">Rhynchobdella haleppensis</emphasis>
Bloch
</taxonomicName>
, in 
<bibRefCitation author="Schneider, J. G." box="[179,353,1339,1364]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refId="ref4909" refString="Schneider, J. G. (1801) M. E. Blochii Systema Ichthyologiae iconibus cx illustratum, post obitum auctoris opus inchoatum absoluit, correxit, interpolavit Jo. Gottlob Schneider. Sanderiano, Berolini [Berlin], 584 pp., 110 pls. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 5475805]" type="book" year="1801">Schneider, 1801</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
